Quark Breaking Changes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  This file documents breaking and/or other changes that might require
  user interaction. Examples include: a user facing structure change; a
  new library call; a change in behaviour.

Changes from 0.1 to 0.2
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o quark_queue_stats{} got a "backend" member.

Changes from 0.2 to 0.3
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o quark_queue_process{} got {uts,ipc,mnt,net}_inonum members.
  o -h on quark-{mon,test,btf} now invokes the manpage instead of usage.

Changes from 0.3 to 0.4
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o quark_queue_get_events(3) was removed in favor of quark_queue_get_event(3).
  o quark_event{} got a new member socket,
    QUARK_EV_SOCK_CONN_{ESTABLISHED,CLOSED}. The probes still have
    some issues so it's mostly experimental.
  o Initial snapshot of process events is not sent anymore. User is
    expected to retrieve them via quark_process_iter(3) if
    desired. QUARK_EV_SNAPHOT and QQ_NO_SNAPSHOT
  o QUARK_EV_SNAPSHOT and QQ_NO_SNAPSHOT are gone.
  o quark_event{} got a cgroup field guarded by QUARK_F_CGROUP.
  o cmdline arguments are now handled via quark_cmdline_iter{} and friends.
  o DNS events were added via QQ_DNS and expressed via quark_packet{}
    in the packet member of quark_event{}.
  o quark-mon(8) got options for socket and dns events: -S and -N.
  o QQ_BYPASS was added for ebpf, with this a client can choose to use
    quark just as bpf loader and access the ring directly. The ring
    event is in quark_event.bypass.
  o Quark can now be linked against system libraries instead of
    embedding its own libbpf and zlib, via make SYSLIB=y.

Changes from 0.4 to 0.5
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o Added support for file events, quark_event{} gets a file member.
  o entity_id was added to quark_process{}.

Changes from 0.5 to 0.6
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o Kubernetes metadata have been added to quark_event{}. See
    quark-mon -K.
  o PTRACE probes have been added via QQ_PTRACE.
  o JSON ECS output has been added via -j in quark-mon(8) and
    quark_event_to_ecs(3).
  o quark_event.filename has been renamed to quark_event.exe, the
    relative pathnames are also now always resolved.
  o quark_event_dump() now prints more fields
  o cgroup2 is now temporarily mounted and unmounted if needed, and
    the process cgroup is in quark_event.cgroup.
  o A bunch of ECS only fields have been added to the JSON output.
     o process.thread.capabilities.{effective,permitted}
     o process.parent.*a
     o container.runtime
     o container.name
     o container.tag
     o container.hash
     o host.hostname
     o host.name
     o host.architecture
     o host.ip
     o host.mac
     o host.boot.id
     o host.os.kernel
     o host.os.name
     o host.os.version
     o host.os.full
     o host.os.release_type
  o quark-mon(8) stats are now printed to stderr.
  o quark_socket{} now has a conn_origin field (SOCK_CONN_*).
  o Lost events incorrect counting in ebpf have been fixed.
  o QQ_MODULE_LOAD has been added and will produce
    quark_event.module_load.
  o QQ_SHM has been added and will produce quark_event.shm.
  o Process environment has been added to quark_event.process->env.
  o QQ_TTY now works outside of QQ_BYPASS.
  o quark_event.time has been added, and it's the time monotonically
    stamped by the backend.
  o Process id changes have been added to quark_event. id_change,
    QUARK_ID_CHANGE_SETSID, QUARK_ID_CHANGE_SETUID...
  o Quark now has a DSL for filtering out events, see
    quark_rule_match_field() and quark_ruleset_append_rule(), for a
    better example check quark-mon(8) -r documentation.
    The grammar can be checked here:
    3ccbe219efead9f1aa310ea140b08715000fcb63
  o quark_process.flags have been revamped, these no longer exist:
    QUARK_F_ENV, QUARK_F_CGROUP, QUARK_F_CONTAINER, QUARK_F_CWD,
    QUARK_F_CMDLINE, QUARK_F_FILENAME, QUARK_F_COMM.
    The user should instead, just compare the pointer against NULL.
  o Aggregation matrix can now be tunned via
    quark_Queue_set_agg_matrix(3).
  o libbpf has been updated.

Changes from 0.6 to 0.7
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  o BPF_CC is gone, just use CLANG='zig cc' now.
